{"author":{"id":"9ce646fd10346788b0ba0bb1d6d4d7df7faf6b71badbb76619d75576ac1df697"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1770798836,"nonce":"PNfc5w6nYbr2Q/gN/vfhnVVDugE=","title":"Silent Elasticsearch failures in production","message":"The Elasticsearch rescue blocks added for test compatibility (Faraday::ConnectionFailed, Errno::ECONNREFUSED) silently swallow connection errors with no logging.\n\nAffected locations:\n- app/models/borrower.rb search_people method - returns empty results\n- app/models/parent_item.rb search method - returns empty results  \n- app/models/conduct.rb reindex_borrower - empty rescue body\n- app/models/item.rb reindex_parent_item (3 locations) - empty rescue body\n- app/models/lending.rb reindex (1 location) - empty rescue body\n\nIn production, if Elasticsearch goes down, search silently returns no results and reindex operations silently fail with no indication to users or operators.\n\nRecommendation: Add Rails.logger.warn to all rescue blocks so ES outages are visible in logs.","files":null}]}